former sen. bill brock also accused the vice president's campaign of deliberate distortions of dole's position that were ``demeaning to the political process.''
brock made his comments as aides said the campaign had hired new producers for its television advertisements in the wake of dole's defeat by bush in last week's new hampshire primary
officials said michael murphy and alex castellanos, who produced a biographical videotape used late last year to introduce dole to the voters, would be joining the campaign. they will replace don ringe
