he said it was time to ``start pointing out how many times george bush has changed his position on taxes. back in october he said he was against any tax increase, a few days later he came out and said well maybe. in november again he said, well i really don't want to and then four days after that he said maybe we'll have to.''
i don't think we're going to be on the defensive on this one. i think we're going to be on the offensive,'' he said
