the use of vinyl for window frames is growing as an alternative to aluminum and wood for home repair and remodeling in the united states, according to a trade association which says its product has grown about 20 percent annually over the last five years
vinyl window frames account for almost a quarter of the 22.5 million replacement windows installed in american homes annually, says julie cahn, executive director of the vinyl window and door institute
